COVID-19 Status 💉 🦠

As of 9:29AM PT today, over 1.5 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 26.7 thousand have died.

In the last day, 511 new infections were reported and 3 deaths. This is trending downwards.

Fortunately, 51.5 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 12 years and older, 82.2% have their 1st shot and 72.3% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is slowing down, but there are 11.3 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~79 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around Dec-18 when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children aged 11 or younger.
